<li id="cite_note-death_riddle-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-death_riddle_8-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/latest_news/110852.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/latest_news/110852.stm" rel="nofollow">"Alexander's death riddle is 'solved'"</a>. BBC. 1998-06-11<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/latest_news/110852.stm" class="external free" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/latest_news/110852.stm" rel="nofollow">http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/latest_news/110852.stm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-05-20</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Alexander%27s+death+riddle+is+%27solved%27&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=1998-06-11&amp;rft.pub=BBC&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F1%2Fhi%2Fhealth%2Flatest_news%2F110852.stm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Alexander_the_Great"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-ref1-9">^ <a href="#cite_ref-ref1_9-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ref1_9-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/eid/vol9no12/03-0288.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/eid/vol9no12/03-0288.htm" rel="nofollow">"Alexander the Great and West Nile Virus Encephalitis"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention" title="Centers for Disease Control and Prevention">Centers for Disease Control and Prevention</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/eid/vol9no12/03-0288.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/eid/vol9no12/03-0288.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/eid/vol9no12/03-0288.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-05-20</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Alexander+the+Great+and+West+Nile+Virus+Encephalitis&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BCenters+for+Disease+Control+and+Prevention%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fncidod%2Feid%2Fvol9no12%2F03-0288.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Alexander_the_Great"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> Alexander probably had greater affection for Achilles than for any other historical figure. <a href="/wiki/Lysimachus" title="Lysimachus">Lysimachus</a>, one of his boyhood tutors, indulged this fancy by some shamelessly ingratiating nomenclature: Alexander he called Achilles, Philip <a href="/wiki/Peleus" title="Peleus">Peleus</a> and himself <a href="/wiki/Phoenix_(Iliad)" title="Phoenix (Iliad)">Phoenix</a>. Certainly, it seems true that Alexander modelled himself to a degree on the central figure of <a href="/wiki/Homer" title="Homer">Homer</a>'s <i><a href="/wiki/Iliad" title="Iliad">Iliad</a></i>: both of them were prone to stewing sulks, and both held their horses in lofty regard. Macedonian society in general, it seems, was self-consciously Homeric, especially in the art of war.</li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <a href="#CITEREFPlutarch1919" title="">Plutarch 1919</a>, §2.1</li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> <a href="#CITEREFPlutarch1919" title="">Plutarch 1919</a>, §2.2–3</li>
<li id="cite_note-BriefLife3-13">^ <a href="#cite_ref-BriefLife3_13-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-BriefLife3_13-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BPlutarch.5D.5D2004"><a href="/wiki/Plutarch" title="Plutarch">Plutarch</a> (2004). Tania Gergel. ed. <i>The Brief Life and Towering Exploits of History's Greatest Conqueror as Told By His Original Biographers</i>. <a href="/wiki/Penguin_Books" title="Penguin Books">Penguin Books</a>. p.&#160;3. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0142001406" class="internal">ISBN 0142001406</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Brief+Life+and+Towering+Exploits+of+History%27s+Greatest+Conqueror+as+Told+By+His+Original+Biographers&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BPlutarch%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BPlutarch%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B3&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BPenguin+Books%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0142001406&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Alexander_the_Great"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> Plutarch (<i>Alexander</i> 3.1,3) claims that Philip seldom slept with Olympias after seeing a snake stretched out at her side as she slept.</li>
<li id="cite_note-BriefLife99-15">^ <a href="#cite_ref-BriefLife99_15-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-BriefLife99_15-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-BriefLife99_15-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BPlutarch.5D.5D2004"><a href="/wiki/Plutarch" title="Plutarch">Plutarch</a> (2004). Tania Gergel. ed. <i>The Brief Life and Towering Exploits of History's Greatest Conqueror as Told By His Original Biographers</i>. <a href="/wiki/Penguin_Books" title="Penguin Books">Penguin Books</a>. p.&#160;99. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0142001406" class="internal">ISBN 0142001406</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Brief+Life+and+Towering+Exploits+of+History%27s+Greatest+Conqueror+as+Told+By+His+Original+Biographers&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BPlutarch%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BPlutarch%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B99&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BPenguin+Books%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0142001406&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Alexander_the_Great"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> Years later, following Alexander's conquest of Gaza, a city directly on the Persian <a href="/wiki/Spice_trade" title="Spice trade">spice trade</a> route, the young king sent back over fifteen tons of <a href="/wiki/Myrrh" title="Myrrh">myrrh</a> to Leonidas as a retort.</li>
<li id="cite_note-BriefLife7-17">^ <a href="#cite_ref-BriefLife7_17-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-BriefLife7_17-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BPlutarch.5D.5D2004"><a href="/wiki/Plutarch" title="Plutarch">Plutarch</a> (2004). Tania Gergel. ed. <i>The Brief Life and Towering Exploits of History's Greatest Conqueror as Told By His Original Biographers</i>. <a href="/wiki/Penguin_Books" title="Penguin Books">Penguin Books</a>. p.&#160;7. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0142001406" class="internal">ISBN 0142001406</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Brief+Life+and+Towering+Exploits+of+History%27s+Greatest+Conqueror+as+Told+By+His+Original+Biographers&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BPlutarch%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BPlutarch%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B7&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BPenguin+Books%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0142001406&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Alexander_the_Great"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.hyperhistory.net/apwh/bios/b2alexandergreat.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.hyperhistory.net/apwh/bios/b2alexandergreat.htm" rel="nofollow">"Alexander the Great"</a>. Hyperhistory.net<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.hyperhistory.net/apwh/bios/b2alexandergreat.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.hyperhistory.net/apwh/bios/b2alexandergreat.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.hyperhistory.net/apwh/bios/b2alexandergreat.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-03-07</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Alexander+the+Great&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Hyperhistory.net&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hyperhistory.net%2Fapwh%2Fbios%2Fb2alexandergreat.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Alexander_the_Great"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
